export const QUESTIONS = {"office_professional":[[{"phase":"situation","question":"How are you currently getting new clients — is it mostly referrals, or do you have any digital presence working for you like SEO or paid search?","goodResponse":"Referral-dependent firms grow unevenly and plateau fast. That tells me there's probably an untapped inbound opportunity we should talk about.","badResponse":"Referrals are great, but we can add digital on top of that.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"When a potential client Googles your firm name or searches for your service in this area, do you know where you're showing up — or not showing up?","goodResponse":"If you don't know, that's usually a sign there's real visibility you're leaving behind. What does your website traffic look like month over month?","badResponse":"SEO is important. We handle that for professional firms.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a qualified prospect in your area is searching for the services you offer and they find a competitor's website first — how many of those engagements are you losing without ever knowing it?","goodResponse":"That invisible leakage is the hardest thing to quantify — you don't see the lost leads. But when we do a search audit, we can usually show the gap pretty clearly.","badResponse":"You're losing leads you don't know about. We can fix that.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your firm was ranking on the first page for your top three service keywords in this market, how many new consultations a month do you think that would generate?","goodResponse":"That's the number that makes the ROI conversation easy. Let me show you what a local SEO and content strategy looks like for a firm at your stage.","badResponse":"We can get you there. Let's talk strategy.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"Does your firm have any active content marketing — blog posts, thought leadership articles, newsletters — or is your online presence mostly a static website?","goodResponse":"A static website is a brochure, not a lead generator. Content is what creates ongoing visibility and positions you as the authority in your space.","badResponse":"Content marketing makes a big difference for professional firms.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"When you meet a prospect at an event and they look you up afterward, what do they find — is your digital presence telling the story you want it to tell?","goodResponse":"Most professionals are surprised when they actually look at their firm through a client's eyes. What would you want a prospect to feel after spending five minutes on your site?","badResponse":"We make sure your digital presence matches your real reputation.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a prospect can't find social proof — testimonials, case studies, published articles, or media mentions — for your firm, how does that affect their confidence in reaching out compared to a competitor with a stronger online story?","goodResponse":"Credibility content is the difference between a warm inbound inquiry and a cold outreach. The firms with strong thought leadership pipelines don't have to sell as hard.","badResponse":"Social proof matters online. We build it for you.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your firm had a consistent stream of relevant content published monthly — articles, case studies, email newsletters — and it was all handled for you, how would that change how you feel about business development?","goodResponse":"That shift from reactive to proactive business development is what content marketing enables. Let me walk you through what a managed content program looks like for your firm.","badResponse":"We do all that for you. Let's scope it out.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"Are you currently running any paid digital advertising — Google Ads, LinkedIn — to bring in new clients, or is your business development entirely relationship-driven?","goodResponse":"Purely relationship-driven growth can work, but it's hard to scale and hard to predict. Let me understand what your client acquisition target looks like.","badResponse":"Paid digital can scale what referrals can't.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Do you have a sense of what your average cost to acquire a new client is right now — including your time spent on networking, proposals, and follow-up?","goodResponse":"Most professionals are surprised how high that number actually is when they calculate it honestly. What does your conversion rate look like from initial meeting to engagement?","badResponse":"We make client acquisition more predictable and measurable.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If your current business development approach isn't generating enough volume to hit your revenue targets — and it's consuming senior partner time to do it — what does that cost the firm in billable hours forgone?","goodResponse":"Partner time spent on BD instead of client work is expensive. The firms that build a marketing engine free their partners to focus on delivery.","badResponse":"BD time has opportunity cost. We build the engine.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If a targeted LinkedIn and Google campaign was bringing qualified leads directly to your intake form each week — without any partner time spent on it — what would that be worth to the firm's growth trajectory?","goodResponse":"That's the math that makes marketing a profit center, not a cost. Let me show you what a targeted campaign for professional services looks like.","badResponse":"We run those campaigns. Let's talk budget.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}]],"tech_company":[[{"phase":"situation","question":"What does your current customer acquisition stack look like — are you running product-led growth, outbound, content, paid, or some combination?","goodResponse":"Interesting mix — it tells me something about where the growth levers are and where there might be gaps or inefficiencies in the funnel right now.","badResponse":"We work with SaaS companies across all those models.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Do you have strong visibility into which marketing channels are actually driving your pipeline — down to MQL source, conversion rate by channel, and CAC by segment?","goodResponse":"Attribution is the thing most marketing teams are flying blind on. If you can't tie spend to pipeline clearly, you're optimizing on gut instead of data.","badResponse":"We build proper attribution models for SaaS companies.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If you're allocating budget to channels that aren't actually converting to revenue — because the attribution isn't clean — what does that misallocation cost you in a $50K or $100K monthly ad spend?","goodResponse":"That's a number that makes most marketing leaders uncomfortable when they actually see it. The waste in unattributed spend is usually significant enough to fund the attribution project twice over.","badResponse":"Misallocated spend is a real problem. We fix attribution.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your CMO had a live dashboard showing exact CAC, LTV, and pipeline contribution by channel — updated daily — how would that change how you make marketing investment decisions?","goodResponse":"That's the operating environment high-growth SaaS companies compete from. Let me walk you through what our growth marketing and analytics stack looks like.","badResponse":"We build those dashboards. Want a demo?","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"What does your content and SEO strategy look like right now — do you have dedicated resources producing content, or is it something that happens when someone has bandwidth?","goodResponse":"Bandwidth-dependent content programs almost always stall. The companies growing organically at scale treat content like a product — dedicated roadmap, consistent output, measured outcomes.","badResponse":"We build content programs that scale with your growth.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Are you currently ranking for the high-intent keywords that your ICP is using when they're actively evaluating solutions like yours — or is your SEO mostly brand-name traffic?","goodResponse":"Brand traffic is vanity, intent traffic is pipeline. If you're not showing up for 'best [your category] software' or '[your problem] solution,' you're missing buyers at the bottom of the funnel.","badResponse":"We build intent-based SEO strategies for SaaS.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If your biggest competitor is ranking on page one for the keywords your buyers use at evaluation stage and you're on page three — how much of your available TAM are you effectively invisible to?","goodResponse":"The math on that is sobering. First-page results capture roughly 90% of clicks — if you're not there, you're competing for scraps while your competitor owns the conversation.","badResponse":"SEO gaps have real pipeline consequences. We close them.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If we could get you ranking in the top three for your five highest-intent keyword clusters within six months, what would that do for your inbound demo request volume?","goodResponse":"That's the pipeline impact we model before we start. Let me walk you through our SaaS SEO methodology and what the ramp looks like.","badResponse":"We can get you there. Let's build the keyword map.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"What does your current brand positioning look like — do you have a clear, differentiated message that resonates with your ICP, or is it something you're still working on?","goodResponse":"A lot of great products are underselling because the positioning hasn't caught up to the value. It tells me there might be a gap between what you've built and how the market perceives it.","badResponse":"Positioning is foundational. We help SaaS companies get it right.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"When your sales team talks to a prospect, do they all tell the same story — same elevator pitch, same objection handling, same value prop — or does it vary from rep to rep?","goodResponse":"Messaging inconsistency is a sales efficiency killer. When every rep tells a different story, the market never builds a clear picture of what you actually are.","badResponse":"We unify messaging across the sales and marketing motion.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If your sales team is losing deals partly because prospects leave confused about your differentiation — and that confusion is rooted in inconsistent positioning — what does that cost you in win rate terms?","goodResponse":"Even a two to three point improvement in win rate compounds dramatically at scale. Clear positioning is one of the highest-leverage investments a growth-stage company can make.","badResponse":"Positioning impacts win rates. We sharpen that for you.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If every sales rep, every landing page, and every piece of content told the same sharp, differentiated story about why you win — what would that do for conversion at every stage of your funnel?","goodResponse":"That's what category-defining companies are built on. Let me show you our brand and messaging sprint process.","badResponse":"We build that messaging framework. Let's talk scope.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}]],"healthcare":[[{"phase":"situation","question":"How are new patients finding your practice right now — are they coming from Google searches, insurance directories, referrals from other providers, or a mix?","goodResponse":"Understanding your patient acquisition mix is the starting point. A lot of practices are heavily dependent on one channel without realizing it.","badResponse":"We help practices diversify their patient acquisition channels.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"When a potential patient Googles your specialty in this area, how are your online reviews comparing to the other practices they're seeing — and do you have a process for generating new reviews consistently?","goodResponse":"Review recency matters as much as review count. A practice with 200 reviews from three years ago often loses to a competitor with 40 fresh reviews from this month.","badResponse":"We build review generation systems for healthcare practices.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a patient chooses another practice because your online reputation looks stale or your reviews are older — how many new patients per month do you think you're losing to that perception gap?","goodResponse":"For most practices, even recovering two to three patients a month from that gap pays for a full year of reputation management. It's a high-ROI problem to solve.","badResponse":"Lost patients are lost revenue. We fix your reputation pipeline.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your practice had a consistent flow of fresh five-star reviews, showed up in the top three results for your specialty in this zip code, and had a website that converted visitors to appointments — what would that do for your monthly new patient count?","goodResponse":"That's the full patient acquisition engine. Let me walk you through what we build for healthcare practices.","badResponse":"We build that. Let's talk about your specialty.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"Does your practice have a social media presence, and if so, who's managing it — a staff member, an outside agency, or is it mostly inactive?","goodResponse":"An inactive or inconsistent social presence sends a signal to potential patients about how the practice operates. What does your current posting frequency look like?","badResponse":"We manage healthcare social media compliantly and consistently.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Has your practice ever had a negative comment or review on social media that sat there without a response — and you only found out about it weeks later?","goodResponse":"Unanswered negative reviews signal to future patients that the practice doesn't engage or care. What does your current review monitoring process look like?","badResponse":"We monitor and respond to reviews for healthcare practices.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a prospective patient reads a negative review with no response from your practice — and then sees a competitor's page where every review gets a thoughtful reply — which practice do they call?","goodResponse":"The engaged practice wins that comparison every time. And the engagement signal is often more persuasive than the star rating itself.","badResponse":"Engagement matters. We make sure you're always represented.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your social presence was active, HIPAA-compliant, and monitored daily — with every review responded to within 24 hours — how much more confident would you feel about what patients see before they call?","goodResponse":"That confidence is exactly what our healthcare marketing clients describe. Let me show you what a managed social and reputation program looks like.","badResponse":"We manage all of that. Let's get started.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"Do you have any paid advertising running right now — Google Ads for your specialty, Facebook ads, or anything targeting patients in your area?","goodResponse":"Healthcare paid search is one of the most competitive and highest-intent digital environments there is. It tells me something about whether you're competing for patients at the bottom of the funnel.","badResponse":"We run compliant, high-ROI paid campaigns for healthcare.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"If you've run Google Ads before, did you find it was hard to track whether those clicks were actually turning into scheduled appointments — or were you just watching spend with no clear outcome visibility?","goodResponse":"That tracking gap is the most common reason healthcare practices pause ads — they can't see the ROI. But the ROI is usually there; it just needs proper measurement to see.","badResponse":"We set up proper call tracking and appointment attribution.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If your competitor is running a well-managed paid search campaign and capturing every patient in your area who types 'dentist near me' or 'cardiologist in [city]' — how much of that demand are you missing?","goodResponse":"In high-competition healthcare markets, the practices running paid search are capturing a disproportionate share of new patients. That's the compounding disadvantage of sitting it out.","badResponse":"You're missing high-intent patients. We capture them for you.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If we ran a campaign that brought in five to ten new patients per month from paid search alone — fully tracked from click to appointment — what would that revenue look like against the ad spend?","goodResponse":"That's the ROI conversation that makes the decision easy. Let me run a quick projection based on your average patient value.","badResponse":"The ROI is usually very strong in healthcare. Let's model it.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}]],"retail_food":[[{"phase":"situation","question":"How are you currently getting new customers through the door — are you running any digital marketing, or is it mostly foot traffic, word of mouth, and whatever Yelp and Google show naturally?","goodResponse":"That's a really common starting point. Organic visibility and word of mouth can get you busy, but they're hard to scale and hard to control.","badResponse":"We help restaurants and retailers add a predictable digital layer to that.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Do you know what your Google Maps ranking looks like for searches like 'coffee shop near me' or 'best brunch in [neighborhood]' — and how that compares to your competitors?","goodResponse":"Most owners are surprised when they look at this objectively. Google Maps placement is often the single highest-leverage marketing variable for a physical location.","badResponse":"We specialize in Google Maps optimization for local businesses.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a local customer searches for what you offer and clicks on the first result — which is a competitor two blocks away — and they go there and become a regular, what does that lost customer represent over a year in revenue?","goodResponse":"The lifetime value of a regular customer is substantial. And the compounding effect of losing dozens of those searches per week is why the ranking gap turns into a revenue gap.","badResponse":"Lost search visibility means lost regulars. We fix the ranking.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your business showed up in the top three results every time someone nearby searched for what you serve — and your profile had fresh photos, current hours, and active reviews — what would that do for your weekday traffic?","goodResponse":"That's the difference between being discovered and being invisible. Let me walk you through what a local visibility program looks like for a business like yours.","badResponse":"We make that happen. Let's talk.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"Do you have any loyalty program or email list built up, or are your repeat customers coming back just out of habit without any structured engagement from you?","goodResponse":"A customer email list is one of the most underutilized assets a local business has. It tells me there's probably revenue sitting in your existing customer base that you haven't activated.","badResponse":"We build loyalty and email programs for local businesses.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"When you have a slow Tuesday or a special event coming up, do you have a way to reach your existing customers directly and get them back in — or does that kind of promotion get scattered across whatever social posts you can pull together?","goodResponse":"Scrambling to fill slow periods with ad-hoc social posts is exhausting and unpredictable. What does your current approach to driving repeat visits look like?","badResponse":"We build the communication engine that fills slow periods reliably.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If your regulars forget about you for two or three weeks because nothing reminded them you exist — and they develop a habit somewhere else during that stretch — what does that cost you in lost revenue from regulars you worked hard to earn?","goodResponse":"Regulars aren't as loyal as they feel — they're habitual, and habits can be replaced. That's why consistent, low-key communication keeps them coming back.","badResponse":"Out of sight, out of mind. We keep you visible to your regulars.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If you had an automated email and SMS program that sent personalized offers to your regulars every two weeks — without you lifting a finger — how much more predictable would your slow periods be?","goodResponse":"Predictable traffic is the thing every owner says they want most. Let me show you what a loyalty and retention program looks like for a location your size.","badResponse":"We automate that whole thing. Let's set it up.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"Are you active on Instagram or TikTok, and if so, are you seeing real engagement and foot traffic from those channels — or posting and hoping?","goodResponse":"Social media for food and retail is one of the highest-ROI channels available, but only when the content is consistent and strategic. Let me understand what your posting looks like right now.","badResponse":"We manage social content for food and retail businesses.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Are you finding it hard to keep up with creating content, responding to comments, and staying visible on social alongside everything else you're running?","goodResponse":"Content burnout is the most common reason local businesses go quiet online — and silence on social sends the same signal as a closed sign. What does your typical content week look like?","badResponse":"We take the content burden off your plate entirely.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If your social presence goes quiet for a few weeks during your busiest season — because you're too busy running the business — what does that mean for the customers who would have discovered you from an Instagram Reel or a tagged photo?","goodResponse":"The irony is that the times you're too busy to post are the times your content would resonate most. That's the discovery gap a managed social program eliminates.","badResponse":"Gaps in posting cost you discovery. We keep it consistent.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your social media was managed professionally — consistent posts, engaging content, comments responded to daily — while you focused entirely on running the business, what would that be worth to you?","goodResponse":"That mental bandwidth is real money. Let me show you what a managed social program looks like for a business like yours — including what kind of content performs best in food and retail.","badResponse":"We handle all of that. Let's talk about your brand.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}]],"trades_contractor":[[{"phase":"situation","question":"How are you currently getting new job leads — are you on HomeAdvisor or Angi, relying on word of mouth, or running any digital marketing of your own?","goodResponse":"Lead aggregators like Angi can work, but you're often bidding against four other contractors and paying for the same lead. It tells me something about how much control you have over your pipeline.","badResponse":"We help contractors build their own lead pipeline instead of renting one.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"When your schedule has a gap between jobs, do you have a way to fill it quickly — or are you back to calling around and hoping something comes through?","goodResponse":"That reactive pipeline is stressful and expensive. What does your typical lead-to-job conversion rate look like when you do get an inquiry?","badResponse":"We build proactive lead pipelines for contractors.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If your crew sits idle for even one day a week because the pipeline isn't full enough, what does that cost you in direct labor expense and opportunity cost?","goodResponse":"A day of idle crew is a very concrete number, and it's one most contractors don't want to calculate because it makes the marketing investment look obvious by comparison.","badResponse":"Idle crew is expensive. Marketing fills that gap.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If you had a steady flow of qualified leads coming in through your own Google presence and a professional website — without paying per lead to an aggregator — how much more predictable would your scheduling be?","goodResponse":"Owning your lead pipeline changes how you negotiate, how you price, and how you plan. Let me show you what that setup looks like for a contractor your size.","badResponse":"We build that for you. Let's talk about your trade.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"What does your online reputation look like right now — how many Google reviews do you have, and when was the last time you actively asked a satisfied customer to leave one?","goodResponse":"Review recency is often the deciding factor when a homeowner is choosing between two contractors. Let me understand what your review generation process looks like.","badResponse":"We build review systems for tradespeople and contractors.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Have you ever lost a job to a competitor who had more reviews or a higher Google rating — even though you know your work is better?","goodResponse":"That's a frustrating position to be in — better work, worse online visibility. The quality of your work doesn't matter until the customer decides to call you.","badResponse":"Online reputation determines who gets the call. We fix that.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If potential customers consistently choose a competitor based on reviews — even for smaller jobs — how does that affect your revenue over the course of a year, and how many of those customers might have become referral sources?","goodResponse":"Every lost customer is a lost referral network too. The compounding effect of a weak online reputation goes far beyond the individual job.","badResponse":"Each lost job means lost referrals too. Reviews matter more than most think.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If we set up an automated review request system that sent every finished customer to your Google profile at the right moment — and you built up 30 or 40 fresh five-star reviews over the next few months — how many more calls do you think you'd get?","goodResponse":"That review volume is often the tipping point between getting ignored and getting called first. Let me show you what the review automation looks like.","badResponse":"We set up that automation. It's simple and effective.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"Do you have a website, and if so, does it have a contact form or a way for customers to request a quote online — or is it basically just a digital business card?","goodResponse":"A static website is a missed conversion opportunity. A well-built contractor site should be generating quote requests around the clock. What does the site look like right now?","badResponse":"We build contractor websites that actually generate leads.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"When a potential customer visits your website, is there a clear reason for them to fill out a form or call right now — or does the site just describe your services without any urgency or call to action?","goodResponse":"Most contractor sites read like a resume instead of a sales page. If a visitor doesn't know exactly what to do next, they close the tab.","badResponse":"We build contractor sites with strong conversion paths.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If your website gets 200 visitors a month but converts at 1% instead of the 5% a well-optimized site could get — how many quote requests per month are you losing to that gap?","goodResponse":"That's eight leads a month you're not getting — and depending on your average job size, that number gets significant quickly.","badResponse":"Low conversion is a revenue leak. We plug it.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your website had a clear value proposition, strong project photos, a simple quote request form, and was optimized to convert visitors — what would getting even five more quote requests per month mean for your business?","goodResponse":"At your close rate, that's real revenue. And it compounds once the site is ranking. Let me show you what a high-converting contractor site looks like.","badResponse":"We build those sites. Let's talk about your trade and target area.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}]],"auto_services":[[{"phase":"situation","question":"How are you currently marketing your dealership or shop — are you running TV, digital, or a mix, and do you have a dedicated marketing budget and someone managing it?","goodResponse":"Automotive marketing is one of the most competitive digital categories out there. Understanding how your budget is structured helps me see where the leverage points are.","badResponse":"We specialize in automotive marketing — digital, local, and conquest.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Do you have visibility into which marketing channels are driving actual floor traffic and service appointments — or are you making budget decisions based on rep recommendations and instinct?","goodResponse":"Most dealers I talk to are surprised how little visibility they have into what's actually working. What does your current reporting look like?","badResponse":"We build proper attribution for auto marketing spend.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If you're spending significantly on TV or radio and can't tie it to sales or ROs — while a competitor is running a leaner, more targeted digital strategy and winning conquest customers — what does that budget inefficiency cost you over a year?","goodResponse":"The cost isn't just the wasted spend — it's the competitor gaining market share while you're paying for impressions that don't convert.","badResponse":"Wasted ad spend is lost profit. We make it accountable.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If you had a marketing setup where every dollar spent was trackable to a vehicle sale or a service RO — and you could optimize toward what's working in real time — how would that change how you make marketing decisions?","goodResponse":"That's the operating environment the top-performing dealers in every market are running. Let me walk you through our automotive marketing analytics framework.","badResponse":"We provide that accountability layer. Let's talk budget and goals.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"What does your online reputation look like across Google, DealerRater, and Cars.com — are you actively managing reviews, or is it mostly organic?","goodResponse":"Reputation is the first filter a car buyer uses now before they even visit a lot. What your review profile looks like on those platforms shapes your traffic before any ad dollar is spent.","badResponse":"We manage automotive reputation across all major review platforms.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Have you had a string of negative reviews from a difficult stretch — maybe a busy period, a staffing change, or a service issue — that are still sitting at the top of your profile and affecting your rating?","goodResponse":"Old negative reviews with no recent positives anchor your rating in a way that's hard to escape without an active review generation strategy. What does the current sentiment distribution look like?","badResponse":"We help dealers recover and protect their review profile.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If your dealership has a 3.8-star rating and your nearest competitor has 4.4 — and a buyer is choosing between you based on online research before they visit — what percentage of those buyers are you not even getting the chance to talk to?","goodResponse":"Research consistently shows that buyers filter out dealers below 4 stars before ever clicking through. A half-star gap translates directly to lost floor traffic.","badResponse":"Star rating differences directly affect floor traffic. We close that gap.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If we built an automated post-transaction review request system into your delivery process — consistently generating fresh five-star reviews — how quickly do you think your rating would move, and what would that do for your incoming lead volume?","goodResponse":"Most dealerships see meaningful rating movement within 60 to 90 days. And the lead volume impact is measurable from the traffic data. Let me show you what that program looks like.","badResponse":"We run those programs. The ROI is very visible. Let's talk.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"Are you running any retargeting or conquest digital campaigns — targeting people who visited your website or are in-market buyers from your trade area — or is your digital mostly broad awareness?","goodResponse":"Conquest and retargeting are where digital pays the highest ROI for automotive. Broad awareness is expensive and hard to measure. Let me understand your current targeting approach.","badResponse":"We specialize in conquest and retargeting for auto dealers.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Do you know how many people visited your website last month, looked at specific vehicle pages, and then left without a conversion — and whether any follow-up marketing reached them afterward?","goodResponse":"Website visitors who don't convert are warm leads walking out the door. Most dealers don't have a systematic way to re-engage them. What does your retargeting setup look like?","badResponse":"We capture and re-engage those website visitors.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a buyer visits your lot's website, looks at a specific pre-owned vehicle page, and you don't follow up with any targeted ads — but your competitor does — who do you think they end up buying from?","goodResponse":"Retargeting is how you stay in the consideration set after that first visit. Without it, you paid to attract a buyer and then handed them to whoever followed up.","badResponse":"Not retargeting is giving buyers away. We fix that.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If every person who visited your website and looked at inventory saw your ads for the next 30 days — tailored to the specific vehicle they viewed — what would that do for your closing rate on those warm leads?","goodResponse":"That's the retargeting edge. Let me walk you through our automotive retargeting program and what typical conversion lift looks like.","badResponse":"We run those retargeting campaigns. It works well in auto. Let's talk.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}]],"financial_services":[[{"phase":"situation","question":"How are your advisors or agents currently building their book of business — is it mostly referrals from existing clients, or do you have any digital lead generation running?","goodResponse":"Referral-dependent growth is common in financial services, but it creates a ceiling. Understanding that mix helps me see where there's an opportunity to build a more predictable pipeline.","badResponse":"We help financial services firms add a digital layer to referral growth.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"When a potential client searches for a financial advisor or insurance agent in this area, is your firm showing up prominently — or are you losing those searches to larger brands and aggregators like NerdWallet?","goodResponse":"Most independent advisors are invisible in local search, and they lose qualified leads to aggregators who then sell them back as paid referrals. What does your current digital presence look like?","badResponse":"We help independent advisors compete in local search.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a high-net-worth prospect in your target market searches 'fee-only financial advisor' and finds a competitor instead of you — and they become a long-term AUM client somewhere else — what does that missed relationship cost you over a decade?","goodResponse":"The lifetime value of a missed HNW client is substantial. And the volume of those invisible misses is what makes the marketing investment so compelling.","badResponse":"Missed clients have long LTV. We help you capture them.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your firm ranked well for local financial advisory searches, had a compliant, compelling web presence, and ran a thought leadership content program that established trust before first contact — how would that change your new client acquisition rate?","goodResponse":"That's the pipeline that the fastest-growing independent advisors are building. Let me walk you through what a financial services digital marketing program looks like.","badResponse":"We build that for financial firms. Let's talk compliance requirements.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"Does your firm have a compliance-approved content and social media program, or have regulatory constraints made it easier to just stay dark on those channels?","goodResponse":"A lot of financial firms opt out of content marketing because compliance feels like too much friction. But the firms that have built compliant programs are seeing real competitive advantage from it.","badResponse":"We run pre-approved, compliant content programs for financial firms.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Are your advisors trying to build personal brands on LinkedIn or other platforms — and running into roadblocks with compliance review or not knowing what they're actually allowed to say?","goodResponse":"That compliance friction often means advisors just give up on social. But LinkedIn is one of the highest-ROI channels for financial professionals when it's done correctly.","badResponse":"We handle the compliance workflow and make LinkedIn productive for advisors.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If your advisors are invisible on LinkedIn while competitors are publishing insights, building audiences, and getting referrals from their content — what's the relationship and pipeline cost of that visibility gap over time?","goodResponse":"LinkedIn compounds. Advisors who've been active for two to three years have networks that generate warm introductions constantly. Starting late means giving up that compounding advantage.","badResponse":"LinkedIn visibility compounds over time. Inaction has a cost.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If every advisor at your firm had a compliance-approved, ghostwritten LinkedIn content program that published consistently without them lifting a finger — what would that do for their visibility and client pipeline in a year?","goodResponse":"That's a real practice-building tool, not just a vanity play. Let me show you what our advisor content program looks like and how the compliance workflow operates.","badResponse":"We run those programs. Compliance-approved from day one. Let's talk.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"Do you have a structured client communication and nurture program — regular newsletters, market updates, event invitations — or is outreach more ad-hoc?","goodResponse":"Consistent client communication is the single biggest driver of referrals and retention in financial services. Understanding the current cadence helps me see the gap.","badResponse":"We build client communication programs for financial services firms.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Have you had clients mention that they feel out of the loop between annual reviews — or worse, that they found out about something important — like a market event or a tax law change — from someone other than you?","goodResponse":"Being the last to tell a client something important damages trust faster than almost anything. What does your current outreach frequency look like between formal review meetings?","badResponse":"Proactive communication builds retention. We make it consistent.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a client gets poached by a competitor who shows up with better communication — quarterly check-ins, market commentary, relevant tax updates — and they leave because they felt neglected, what does that client represent in AUM and future referrals?","goodResponse":"Client attrition in financial services is almost always a communication problem before it becomes a performance problem. The advisor who stays top of mind keeps the relationship.","badResponse":"Communication prevents attrition. We build the cadence.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If every one of your clients received a personalized, branded market update and relevant content piece every month — handled entirely by us and approved by your compliance team — how would that change your retention rate and your referral volume?","goodResponse":"That consistent presence is what drives the 'by the way, my friend is looking for an advisor' conversations. Let me walk you through our advisor communication program.","badResponse":"We build that program for you. Let's talk scale and compliance.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}]],"real_estate":[[{"phase":"situation","question":"How are your agents currently generating leads — are they relying on Zillow and Realtor.com, referrals, open houses, or do you have a brokerage-level digital marketing program?","goodResponse":"Lead portal dependency is expensive and creates a race to the bottom on response time. Understanding the current mix tells me where the brokerage has leverage.","badResponse":"We help brokerages build lead generation they own and control.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Are your agents happy with the quality of leads they're getting, or are they buying internet leads from aggregators, calling 50 people, and barely converting — making the lead cost feel impossible to justify?","goodResponse":"That aggregator lead math is brutal — high cost, low conversion, commodity competition. What does your average lead-to-transaction rate look like from those sources?","badResponse":"We build lead programs with better ROI than the portals.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If your top agents are burning time on low-quality internet leads — and the frustration drives some of them to consider hanging their license at a competitor — what does the recruiting and replacement cost of losing a producing agent look like?","goodResponse":"Agent retention is directly tied to their income, and their income is tied to lead quality. The brokerage that solves the lead problem keeps its best agents.","badResponse":"Bad leads drive agent attrition. We solve both problems.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If the brokerage generated warm, exclusive, pre-educated seller and buyer leads through organic and paid digital — leads that converted at two to three times the portal rate — what would that do for agent satisfaction and production?","goodResponse":"That's the lead quality that keeps your best agents loyal and attracts new talent. Let me walk you through what a brokerage-level digital lead program looks like.","badResponse":"We build those programs for brokerages. Let's talk market.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"What does your brokerage brand look like online — do you have a consistent visual identity, strong social presence, and a website that reflects the caliber of your team?","goodResponse":"Brokerage brand matters enormously in recruiting and in how clients choose an agent. Let me understand what that brand presence looks like today.","badResponse":"We build real estate brokerage brands that attract agents and clients.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"When a high-producing agent is considering your brokerage versus a competitor, and they Google both of you — does your digital presence make a compelling case for why they should join you?","goodResponse":"Most brokerages lose recruiting conversations they could have won purely on brand presentation. What impression does a top agent get when they look you up today?","badResponse":"We make sure your brokerage looks like the right choice online.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If you lose one top-producing agent to a competitor with a stronger brand presence — and that agent closes 20 deals a year — what does that mean in GCI and in the cultural signal it sends to the rest of your team?","goodResponse":"A defection always has ripple effects. The brand investment that wins that agent instead of losing them pays for itself on the first sale they make under your roof.","badResponse":"Losing producers is expensive. Brand is part of the retention tool.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your brokerage had a polished, professional brand identity — great website, consistent social presence, compelling agent value proposition visible online — how would that change your recruiting conversations?","goodResponse":"Brand is a recruiting asset that works while you sleep. Let me walk you through what a brokerage brand refresh and content program looks like.","badResponse":"We build that brand presence for brokerages. Let's talk scope.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"How are you currently marketing your listings — do you use professional photography, video walkthroughs, 3D tours, and paid social promotion, or does it vary by agent and price point?","goodResponse":"Listing marketing quality has become a differentiator for the seller experience. Understanding the current standard helps me see where there's consistency or a gap.","badResponse":"We help brokerages standardize and elevate their listing marketing.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Have you had sellers question the marketing effort on their listing — or compare it to what a competing agent was offering — during a listing appointment?","goodResponse":"Listing marketing is now a competitive battleground in listing presentations. What does your current marketing deck look like when you walk into a seller appointment?","badResponse":"We build listing marketing packages that win presentations.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If you lose a listing appointment to a competing agent who showed a more compelling marketing plan — and that listing sells for a significant commission — how many of those listings a year are you losing to a better-presented marketing story?","goodResponse":"Even one or two lost listings per agent per year adds up to real GCI. And the seller experience ripples into reviews and referrals for the next listing.","badResponse":"Lost listings are lost referrals too. Better marketing wins more.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If every listing your agents took came with a branded, professional marketing package — video, 3D tour, targeted social promotion — built and delivered by us, how would that change your listing win rate?","goodResponse":"That marketing edge is the kind of thing sellers remember and talk about. Let me walk you through what our brokerage listing marketing program delivers.","badResponse":"We produce those packages. Let's talk volume and pricing.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}]]};
